1
00:00:36,039 --> 00:00:38,600
My precious items are all wet.

2
00:00:38,679 --> 00:00:40,520
This is the only copy.

3
00:00:40,759 --> 00:00:42,600
The only one in the whole world.

4
00:00:43,640 --> 00:00:44,439
Professor Lu,

5
00:00:44,560 --> 00:00:46,840
could you teach me a few more words on the rubbing?

6
00:00:46,840 --> 00:00:49,000
This ancient seal script inscription...

7
00:00:49,200 --> 00:00:52,079
...is different from our modern writing.

8
00:00:52,479 --> 00:00:54,679
It's a Pictogram.

9
00:00:54,679 --> 00:00:56,399
You need to use your imagination.

10
00:00:56,640 --> 00:00:57,200
Okay.

11
00:00:57,200 --> 00:00:58,960
Try to recognize these first few characters.

12
00:00:59,240 --> 00:01:01,200
And slowly work your way down.

13
00:01:01,840 --> 00:01:03,759
Past life's fortune fallen,

14
00:01:04,879 --> 00:01:08,040
precious treasure lost.

15
00:01:08,040 --> 00:01:11,760
Hidden deep with relics,

16
00:01:11,760 --> 00:01:14,599
to Haoli's tomb forever bound.

17
00:01:14,920 --> 00:01:18,359
To Haoli's tomb forever bound.

18
00:01:19,079 --> 00:01:20,840
Grass radical over "high" makes "Hao".

19
00:01:21,040 --> 00:01:21,840
Haoli.

20
00:01:21,840 --> 00:01:23,079
To Haoli's tomb forever bound. Haoli.

21
00:01:23,079 --> 00:01:24,519
On this tomb-guarding stele,

22
00:01:24,840 --> 00:01:26,480
having these few lines should be enough.

23
00:01:27,280 --> 00:01:29,079
The rest of the messy characters...

24
00:01:29,359 --> 00:01:31,000
...should all be the epitaph.

25
00:01:32,480 --> 00:01:33,120
Old Chen,

26
00:01:33,120 --> 00:01:34,400
this epitaph...

27
00:01:34,799 --> 00:01:36,840
...should be written on a tombstone.

28
00:01:37,319 --> 00:01:40,079
A tomb-guarding stele is meant to guard the tomb, right?

29
00:01:40,280 --> 00:01:41,560
These two types of content...

30
00:01:41,560 --> 00:01:43,200
...why are they written on one stele?

31
00:01:43,840 --> 00:01:44,879
It's very strange.

32
00:01:45,959 --> 00:01:48,159
Could it be that on the tomb-guarding stele...

33
00:01:48,159 --> 00:01:49,480
...we missed some information?

34
00:01:50,439 --> 00:01:51,879
That shouldn't be.

35
00:01:53,079 --> 00:01:54,799
Aren't all the characters right here?

36
00:01:54,799 --> 00:01:56,480
I've already explained them to everyone.

37
00:01:56,760 --> 00:01:57,680
There isn't any...

38
00:01:57,680 --> 00:01:59,400
...information about the underground palace or tomb in here.

39
00:02:42,400 --> 00:02:43,280
What's up?

40
00:02:43,840 --> 00:02:45,439
You've had your eyes closed for a while.

41
00:02:46,080 --> 00:02:47,479
Master Lu has been studying it for a while too.

42
00:02:48,000 --> 00:02:49,199
Did you find anything?

43
00:02:49,840 --> 00:02:50,360
No.

44
00:02:51,560 --> 00:02:53,240
There are too many characters.

45
00:02:53,439 --> 00:02:54,000
How about this?

46
00:02:54,319 --> 00:02:55,479
Let me tell you about it,

47
00:02:55,479 --> 00:02:56,960
and you can help me think it over.

48
00:02:57,319 --> 00:02:57,960
Forget it, forget it.

49
00:02:58,439 --> 00:03:00,199
You're just mocking me with a straight face.

50
00:03:00,479 --> 00:03:01,639
What do I know about this?

51
00:03:01,840 --> 00:03:02,879
I'm only good at stoking the fire.

52
00:03:04,120 --> 00:03:04,919
Chen Youxi,

53
00:03:05,719 --> 00:03:07,120
do you want to go back and take a look?

54
00:03:07,599 --> 00:03:08,919
I keep feeling something isn't right.

55
00:03:09,039 --> 00:03:10,240
The Xuanji diagram is wrong too.

56
00:03:12,080 --> 00:03:13,080
Otherwise, let's go back and check.

57
00:03:18,319 --> 00:03:19,400
What's wrong with those birds?

58
00:03:19,639 --> 00:03:20,479
Have they gone crazy too?

59
00:03:21,199 --> 00:03:23,280
Eagle owls flying away in flocks like this...

60
00:03:23,879 --> 00:03:25,240
...must mean they're threatened by something.

61
00:03:48,520 --> 00:03:49,719
I'm gonna get some sleep first.

62
00:03:49,879 --> 00:03:50,879
Take your time eating.

63
00:03:51,840 --> 00:03:53,000
Going to sleep right after eating?

64
00:03:55,080 --> 00:03:57,599
Y-You're not afraid of indigestion?

65
00:03:58,479 --> 00:03:59,479
Him, indigestion?

66
00:04:01,000 --> 00:04:02,120
Then you don't know him at all.

67
00:04:02,639 --> 00:04:04,000
Back when Fatty could eat the most,

68
00:04:04,000 --> 00:04:05,280
he'd eat half a sheep in one meal,

69
00:04:05,280 --> 00:04:06,000
drink two pints of liquor,

70
00:04:06,000 --> 00:04:07,080
and fall right asleep.

71
00:04:07,120 --> 00:04:08,280
And in the middle of the night,

72
00:04:08,479 --> 00:04:09,639
he'd wake up hungry.

73
00:04:09,879 --> 00:04:10,240
Okay.

74
00:04:10,240 --> 00:04:10,919
Professor Lu.

75
00:04:10,919 --> 00:04:13,520
Teach me a couple more words before bed.

76
00:04:13,840 --> 00:04:14,919
Alright, alright.

77
00:04:16,360 --> 00:04:19,079
Tomorrow, you can teach me some English too.

78
00:04:19,439 --> 00:04:20,920
When I have free time, I'll go abroad

79
00:04:20,920 --> 00:04:22,199
and hang out with you.

80
00:04:26,279 --> 00:04:28,279
Look, isn't it beautiful?

81
00:04:30,680 --> 00:04:32,639
Is it because you've stayed abroad so long

82
00:04:32,879 --> 00:04:35,040
that you rarely see stars like this in the wild?

83
00:04:35,279 --> 00:04:37,639
Do you have some misunderstanding about being abroad?

84
00:04:39,000 --> 00:04:39,879
Abroad, besides those

85
00:04:39,879 --> 00:04:41,759
big cities you can name,

86
00:04:42,120 --> 00:04:43,720
everywhere else is pretty wide open.

87
00:04:45,639 --> 00:04:46,839
When I was little,

88
00:04:47,199 --> 00:04:48,800
my dad used to drive our whole family

89
00:04:48,800 --> 00:04:50,279
to the suburbs to see my grandpa.

90
00:04:51,120 --> 00:04:52,800
Back then, Grandpa always said

91
00:04:53,600 --> 00:04:55,319
the moon he saw when he was young

92
00:04:55,839 --> 00:04:57,519
was bigger and rounder.

93
00:04:59,319 --> 00:05:00,920
He must have been homesick then.

94
00:05:02,519 --> 00:05:03,439
Maybe.

95
00:05:04,639 --> 00:05:05,920
My grandpa lived in the suburbs,

96
00:05:06,120 --> 00:05:07,279
didn't speak the language,

97
00:05:08,240 --> 00:05:09,600
and rarely interacted with anyone.

98
00:05:10,480 --> 00:05:11,480
As he got older,

99
00:05:11,680 --> 00:05:13,040
his personality became even more eccentric.

100
00:05:13,720 --> 00:05:15,040
He was also very short-tempered with my mom.

101
00:05:15,600 --> 00:05:17,040
But he was always very good to me.

102
00:05:17,399 --> 00:05:19,120
He'd always tell me bedtime stories.

103
00:05:19,759 --> 00:05:20,519
What kind of stories?

104
00:05:22,439 --> 00:05:25,120
Just things from his past.

105
00:05:26,800 --> 00:05:28,480
Then those were ghost stories.

106
00:05:32,920 --> 00:05:34,680
Tell me about them when you have time.

107
00:05:35,079 --> 00:05:36,800
I want to hear the stories you heard as a kid.

108
00:05:37,199 --> 00:05:38,959
Sure, anytime.

109
00:05:50,199 --> 00:05:51,279
Get some rest early.

110
00:05:51,439 --> 00:05:52,120
Okay.

111
00:05:52,279 --> 00:05:52,920
Good night.

112
00:05:52,920 --> 00:05:53,639
Good night.

113
00:06:03,399 --> 00:06:04,120
You...

114
00:06:04,399 --> 00:06:05,439
I'll go on night watch.

115
00:06:07,120 --> 00:06:08,839
Stay safe. Come back soon.

116
00:06:08,839 --> 00:06:09,639
Don't worry.

117
00:06:11,639 --> 00:06:12,319
Good night.

118
00:06:13,040 --> 00:06:13,720
Good night.

119
00:06:52,680 --> 00:06:54,639
Staff Officer He! Fatty!

120
00:06:55,240 --> 00:06:55,600
What's wrong?

121
00:06:55,600 --> 00:06:56,480
What's wrong? Did something happen?

122
00:06:56,560 --> 00:06:57,959
Hurry, hurry, hurry up!

123
00:06:58,319 --> 00:06:59,720
Follow me! Come with me!

124
00:07:00,160 --> 00:07:00,920
Wh-What's wrong?

125
00:07:00,920 --> 00:07:02,000
Did something else happen?

126
00:07:02,199 --> 00:07:03,079
Turn off the lights.

127
00:07:09,720 --> 00:07:11,319
This painting is really beautiful.

128
00:07:11,800 --> 00:07:13,120
It's even fluorescent.

129
00:07:13,319 --> 00:07:16,639
Th-This probably isn't a painting.

130
00:07:18,199 --> 00:07:19,920
It's a map.

131
00:07:21,240 --> 00:07:21,920
A map?

132
00:07:23,639 --> 00:07:25,000
Under the bright sun,

133
00:07:25,000 --> 00:07:27,000
we stared right at it and didn't notice.

134
00:07:27,279 --> 00:07:28,480
But in the pitch black,

135
00:07:28,920 --> 00:07:30,319
it gives you a surprise.

136
00:07:31,319 --> 00:07:32,519
This should be fluorite.

137
00:07:33,120 --> 00:07:34,839
The light was too strong before, so we didn't notice.

138
00:07:38,040 --> 00:07:39,120
This sacred path

139
00:07:39,120 --> 00:07:40,000
should be that valley

140
00:07:40,000 --> 00:07:41,639
called Gu Valley.

141
00:07:42,800 --> 00:07:43,720
Look at this map.

142
00:07:44,879 --> 00:07:45,759
This old King of Dian

143
00:07:45,759 --> 00:07:47,560
must have been crazy about becoming an immortal.

144
00:07:47,839 --> 00:07:49,920
He planned to build this palace up in the sky.

145
00:07:50,240 --> 00:07:51,920
Why didn't he just immigrate to the moon?

146
00:07:52,800 --> 00:07:54,399
Their Duan family is really something.

147
00:07:55,920 --> 00:07:56,720
Whose family?

148
00:07:58,399 --> 00:07:59,720
You're so uncultured.

149
00:08:00,079 --> 00:08:02,040
One Yang Finger, haven't you heard of it?

150
00:08:02,600 --> 00:08:03,680
Good lord.

151
00:08:04,040 --> 00:08:05,040
L-Look at this, look at this.

152
00:08:05,040 --> 00:08:06,839
Look at those lines, can you see them?

153
00:08:07,079 --> 00:08:09,240
Don't they look like the Six Meridians Divine Sword?

154
00:08:11,879 --> 00:08:13,480
That's called a Water Dragon Halo.

155
00:08:13,680 --> 00:08:14,839
That water dragon

156
00:08:15,279 --> 00:08:17,079
is just a waterfall with a heavy flow.

157
00:08:17,399 --> 00:08:20,000
That kind of halo is the rising water vapor,

158
00:08:20,000 --> 00:08:22,279
a rainbow created by the refraction of light.

159
00:08:22,759 --> 00:08:24,279
It has form but no substance.

160
00:08:24,279 --> 00:08:26,160
The ancients called it the Immortal Bridge.

161
00:08:26,439 --> 00:08:29,040
It's completely impossible to build a structure on it.

162
00:08:29,399 --> 00:08:32,240
The palace on this map probably isn't the royal tomb,

163
00:08:32,759 --> 00:08:36,480
but the tomb's surface sacrificial facility called Ming Pavilion.

164
00:08:37,120 --> 00:08:37,919
Ming Pavilion?

165
00:08:38,559 --> 00:08:40,960
Old Chen, if what you say is true,

166
00:08:41,080 --> 00:08:42,919
according to the Qin and Han systems,

167
00:08:43,159 --> 00:08:45,039
the underground palace of the royal tomb

168
00:08:45,240 --> 00:08:46,200
should be located

169
00:08:46,200 --> 00:08:49,360
ten zhang below this Ming Pavilion.

170
00:08:49,399 --> 00:08:50,480
This kind of custom

171
00:08:50,480 --> 00:08:52,600
continued all the way to the late Qing Dynasty.

172
00:08:53,840 --> 00:08:55,840
If it's a Ming Pavilion used for sacrifices,

173
00:08:55,840 --> 00:08:57,879
that means after the King of Dian died,

174
00:08:58,159 --> 00:08:59,159
at regular intervals,

175
00:08:59,159 --> 00:09:01,440
people would go into the Ming Pavilion to hold sacrifices.

176
00:09:01,879 --> 00:09:04,240
But... but the area around the King of Dian's tomb

177
00:09:04,240 --> 00:09:06,679
is covered in everlasting poisonous miasma.

178
00:09:07,000 --> 00:09:08,120
How did they get in?

179
00:09:08,799 --> 00:09:11,159
Could there be some secret passage?

180
00:09:12,480 --> 00:09:14,679
These two symmetrical toads, one above and one below,

181
00:09:14,960 --> 00:09:16,639
are very likely the passage used during sacrifices

182
00:09:16,639 --> 00:09:18,840
to pass through the poisonous miasma from underground.

183
00:09:19,080 --> 00:09:20,919
The strange mouths of these toads should be the gates.

184
00:09:21,639 --> 00:09:22,799
As long as we are in Gu Valley

185
00:09:22,799 --> 00:09:23,759
and find this place,

186
00:09:24,240 --> 00:09:26,039
we can enter the King of Dian's tomb.

187
00:09:26,960 --> 00:09:27,879
Quite a harvest.

188
00:09:28,600 --> 00:09:30,879
We finally have some information on the King of Dian's tomb.

189
00:10:03,879 --> 00:10:05,399
Bugs! Bugs!

190
00:10:05,879 --> 00:10:06,759
Miasma water stingers!

191
00:10:07,120 --> 00:10:07,720
Bugs? What's wrong?

192
00:10:07,919 --> 00:10:08,559
Old Chen, what's wrong?

193
00:10:08,559 --> 00:10:09,440
Miasma water stingers!

194
00:10:13,480 --> 00:10:14,159
Don't move.

195
00:10:15,159 --> 00:10:16,279
It's festering.

196
00:10:21,000 --> 00:10:21,840
His fever is too high.

197
00:10:22,159 --> 00:10:23,039
Staff Officer He!

198
00:10:25,000 --> 00:10:26,240
Hurry! Why is he so hot?

199
00:10:26,240 --> 00:10:27,360
Chen Youxi, lift it up.

200
00:10:27,360 --> 00:10:28,240
Let him get some air. Okay.

201
00:10:28,360 --> 00:10:30,039
Come on, come on.

202
00:10:32,879 --> 00:10:33,559
Shutong!

203
00:10:47,240 --> 00:10:48,080
It's infected.

204
00:10:48,360 --> 00:10:49,320
We need to treat the wound immediately.

205
00:10:49,679 --> 00:10:50,279
Yeah.

206
00:10:50,559 --> 00:10:51,799
We know we need to treat it fast.

207
00:10:52,039 --> 00:10:53,080
But our first aid kit...

208
00:10:53,080 --> 00:10:54,559
Isn't it feeding the fish in the cave?

209
00:10:55,159 --> 00:10:55,960
Cool him down first.

210
00:10:57,600 --> 00:10:59,279
I learned in a wilderness first aid class before...

211
00:11:00,080 --> 00:11:01,080
In his condition,

212
00:11:01,080 --> 00:11:02,240
he might have cerebral edema.

213
00:11:02,759 --> 00:11:04,000
If we don't bring his fever down soon,

214
00:11:04,639 --> 00:11:05,799
he's in danger of suffocating.

215
00:11:06,679 --> 00:11:08,000
Wh-What do we do then?

216
00:11:09,240 --> 00:11:10,399
Let's treat the wound first.

217
00:11:10,399 --> 00:11:10,879
Fatty,

218
00:11:11,360 --> 00:11:12,159
go boil a pot of water.

219
00:11:12,159 --> 00:11:13,039
Put some salt in it.

220
00:11:13,039 --> 00:11:14,320
Then find a small tree root and grind it up.

221
00:11:14,600 --> 00:11:15,799
Wrap it in a clean cloth,

222
00:11:15,799 --> 00:11:16,399
and boil it in the water.

223
00:11:16,399 --> 00:11:17,600
Once it's done, apply it to the wound

224
00:11:17,600 --> 00:11:18,519
to draw out all the pus.

225
00:11:18,519 --> 00:11:19,720
Okay, okay, I got it.

226
00:11:19,720 --> 00:11:21,039
Boil... boil water, salt water.

227
00:11:22,360 --> 00:11:24,000
No, we must bring his fever down fast.

228
00:11:24,720 --> 00:11:25,519
Bugleweed.

229
00:11:25,960 --> 00:11:27,559
If we can't find a willow tree,

230
00:11:27,720 --> 00:11:29,080
bugleweed might work.

231
00:11:29,159 --> 00:11:29,480
Bugleweed?

232
00:11:29,480 --> 00:11:30,159
Yes.

233
00:11:30,200 --> 00:11:31,000
What is it?

234
00:11:31,200 --> 00:11:32,320
The locals call it...

235
00:11:32,639 --> 00:11:34,360
call it bugleweed.

236
00:11:34,679 --> 00:11:35,480
Bugleweed.

237
00:11:35,480 --> 00:11:36,080
Bugleweed.

238
00:11:36,080 --> 00:11:36,679
Right.

239
00:11:36,879 --> 00:11:38,399
It's a short plant,

240
00:11:38,639 --> 00:11:40,679
with a small cluster of purple flowers on top.

241
00:11:40,679 --> 00:11:41,559
I'll draw it for you.

242
00:11:41,799 --> 00:11:42,960
This plant is very common.

243
00:11:43,360 --> 00:11:44,320
Tell you what, I'll go with you.

244
00:11:44,320 --> 00:11:46,080
No need, I'll find it myself.

245
00:11:46,159 --> 00:11:46,679
Wait.

246
00:11:46,679 --> 00:11:48,080
Earlier, in the river valley we passed through,

247
00:11:48,080 --> 00:11:48,840
I saw some.

248
00:11:49,080 --> 00:11:49,840
Are you sure?

249
00:11:49,840 --> 00:11:50,600
I'm sure.

250
00:11:52,960 --> 00:11:53,759
Here. Officer He,

251
00:11:53,840 --> 00:11:55,840
that place is covered in thick white mist.

252
00:11:55,840 --> 00:11:57,159
Will you be okay going alone?

253
00:11:57,159 --> 00:11:58,080
I'll be fine, don't worry.

254
00:11:58,480 --> 00:11:59,440
Take good care of Old Chen.

255
00:11:59,559 --> 00:12:00,399
Before I get back,

256
00:12:00,440 --> 00:12:01,639
you must bring his temperature down.

257
00:12:02,200 --> 00:12:03,159
Be careful.
